args: I decided to tell my new friends the truth—\nthe ENTIRE truth—of my story.

What if someone made this decision?
What if a certain event unfolded thusly?
Such possibilities form the roots of the
alternate worlds of which I speak.
At this moment, I am projecting my\nconsciousness to you from another world.
But does your body not stand before us?
It is but a simulacrum created from mana.\nWhen that mana is no more, it will vanish.
Whoa, the look-alike went all...flickery!\nYou all right, lady?!
Go! Waste no time on me.\nI will follow as soon as—
Gone again. Ain't nothin' about that\nwoman what makes a damn bit of sense.
This certainly explains why I perceived\nyou as being composed from mana.
So you winked out back then because\nyou emptied the ol' mana tank?
No. When the Other's power reawakened,\nthe channel I used to reach this world\nwas severed.
Without a channel, I could not even send\nmy thoughts here, let alone manifest\nthis form.
So this ＂channel＂ you use to cross the\nspace between worlds acts as a bridge\nof sorts between existences?
That is certainly one way to attempt\nan understanding of it, yes.
But under normal circumstances,\nit is not possible to reach a specific\nalternate world of your choosing.
Yeah. I mean, there's gotta be\nabout a zillion of these things, right?\nHow would you even sift through 'em?
Locating any specific one would be\nakin to finding the proverbial needle.
Which is why it was thought impossible.\n...But the Dawnshard changed all that.
Do you mind telling us more\nabout the Dawnshard?
The Dawnshard is a Sacred Shard that\npossesses the power to alter causality.
Its power is extraordinary, and its limits—\nif it even has any—are not yet known.
Even having wielded it, I do not know\nthe full extent of its capabilities.
You always mess around with dangerous\ndoodads like that? Big hobby for you?
If an item will help me slay the Other,\nI care not about the consequences\nit may have on myself.
...You're a bit different from our Zethia.
The Zethia I know is...less intense.
The two of us have led very different lives.
After all, the situation on this world\nis very different from that of my own.
What's it like on your world?
On my world, the New Alberian Army\nwas routed by the Dyrenell Empire.
You did. The Dyrenell Emperor was able\nto manipulate dragons into laying waste\nto all of humanity.
I assume this emperor of yours\nwas actually Morsayati?
In this world, the Other was using my\nsister as his vessel, but what happened\nin yours?
I mean, since you're here, he must be\nusing someone else.

That was how the Dyrenell Empire was
able to take control of the dragons.
Because his vessel—my brother—was
pactbound with so many of them.
Wait. So the person who destroyed\nyour entire world was...me?
